29:42.092 --> 29:44.026
<i>Thanks, mom.</i>

29:44.128 --> 29:46.295
Will you teach me?

29:46.363 --> 29:48.631
As soon as you wash
your pretty little face.

29:48.698 --> 29:53.136
A selmer.
Thank you, sweetheart,
I've been missing a clarinet.

29:53.203 --> 29:57.306
Did you know that your daddy
worked his way through college
playing in a band?

29:57.374 --> 30:00.643
My daddy? No.
Major squarehead?

30:00.710 --> 30:04.947
<i>Oh, yeah.
I found that in a pawn
shop along with-</i>

30:05.149 --> 30:07.716
For alexandra.

30:09.186 --> 30:12.988
It's 'cause you're so smart
and you see things
so clearly and-

30:13.056 --> 30:16.325
Well, you can be
the family historian.
Thank you, mom.

30:16.393 --> 30:18.994
It's got film
and flashbulbs and-

30:19.062 --> 30:21.330
Well, you just pose us
and shoot away.

30:24.668 --> 30:26.769
Mom, what did you get?

30:26.836 --> 30:31.006
I get to make us
a indoor picnic.

30:36.746 --> 30:39.515
All right, now we'll see
who's hot and who's not.

30:39.583 --> 30:41.517
