those reports deeper
than the moscow subway.

36:51.120 --> 36:53.922
Do you have any children,
mr. Stevens?

36:53.990 --> 36:57.125
Four. I know
what you're thinking.

37:09.639 --> 37:12.206
My oldest daughter wants
to form a test ban club
right here on the base.

37:12.274 --> 37:14.208
Sometimes I feel
that way myself.

37:14.276 --> 37:16.645
Think we ought to join?
No.

37:26.656 --> 37:29.357
You sure?
No.

37:29.424 --> 37:32.827
Let me have another one.

37:33.162 --> 37:37.231
my heart I can't control

37:37.299 --> 37:41.870
you're, oh, my very soul

37:42.171 --> 37:44.388
my only prayer will be

37:44.674 --> 37:47.575
someday you'll care for me

37:47.643 --> 37:51.913
but it's only

37:51.981 --> 37:54.315
make

37:54.684 --> 37:57.318
believe

38:03.092 --> 38:05.093
Uh-oh, here comes
a stop sign.

38:08.430 --> 38:10.364
Time to go, carly.

38:10.432 --> 38:12.366
I want to stay.

38:12.434 --> 38:15.369
This gal's a real dynamo, major.
If we harness her energy,

38:15.437 --> 38:17.939
We won't need reactors.

38:18.941 --> 38:20.875
Come on, daddy.
Dance with me.

38:20.943 --> 38:23.377
Time to go.
Now. Let's go.

38:23.445 --> 38:26.447
Then I'll dance
by myself.

38:58.197 --> 39:00.248
That is an exceptional woman.

39:03.418 --> 39:05.419
No!

39:08.257 --> 39:11.025
Something should
be done about this.

39:11.093 --> 39:16.264
Yeah, well, I can always
requisition another one.

39:17.432 --> 39:19.768
You're a pig.

39:52.634 --> 39:57.738
Well, you know,
when you're just sitting around
and you're not doing anything-

39:57.807 --> 40:00.574
A moment of time
when nothing's happening.

40:00.642 --> 40:02.576
Mm-hmm.

40:02.644 --> 40:08.249
Well, I call that a "noment."

40:08.317 --> 40:12.586
And then when it's
really hot and you're too
lazy to get up and do anything,

40:12.654 --> 40:15.924
Well, I call that
a "sloment."

40:15.991 --> 40:19.327
A "sloment," huh?
What do you call this?

40:21.595 --> 40:23.596
A tongue kiss.

40:30.437 --> 40:32.605
People were
laughing at you.

40:32.774 --> 40:34.607
Oh, just because you never
have any fun doesn't mean...

40:34.675 --> 40:36.709
You have to spend
your entire life ruining mine.

40:36.778 --> 40:39.212
Son of a bitch.

40:39.280 --> 40:41.948
Why is mom all wet?
She had an accident.

41:19.253 --> 41:22.755
Hi, daddy.

42:06.317 --> 42:08.168
<i>Ten hut.</i>

42:08.236 --> 42:10.503
Ten hut.
As you were.

42:10.571 --> 42:13.006
How's it going, hank?
Busy, sir.

42:13.074 --> 42:15.842
Well, you're going
to be a lot busier.

42:15.910 --> 42:18.678
We just got word that some
seismologists in finland
have detected evidence...

42:18.746 --> 42:21.681
That the soviets have detonated
an above-ground device.

42:21.749 --> 42:24.351
The brass must be thrilled.
We're off the bench and back
in the ball game.

42:24.418 --> 42:26.519
You bet your ass we are.

42:26.587 --> 42:30.023
Everything we do from now on
becomes that much more vital.

42:30.091 --> 42:32.025
Those bastards push in
a pile of chips,

42:32.093 --> 42:34.861
We better be able to raise
the bet, right?
Right.

42:34.929 --> 42:40.700
We can maximize
our opportunities
real quick, especially you.

42:40.768 --> 42:44.537
As of 0800 hours Friday,
4, 28, you are t.D.Y.
To operations h.Q...

42:44.605 --> 42:46.539
At the nevada test site
in mercury.

42:46.607 --> 42:49.042
To what do I owe
this honor, sir?

42:49.110 --> 42:53.546
Stevens from the a.E.C.
He was real impressed with you.

42:53.614 --> 42:57.117
You get a clean slate
to start with this time.

43:00.421 --> 43:03.489
I knew vince johnson
wasn't such a bad guy.

43:03.557 --> 43:05.491
This is a real
vote of confidence in your-

43:05.559 --> 43:08.494
Carly, do you
remember your bible?

43:08.562 --> 43:13.166
Of course I remember my bible.
You know grandpa was a preacher.

43:13.234 --> 43:18.071
All right. How did
david steal bathsheba
away from her husband?

43:20.408 --> 43:23.743
He bought her a drink.
No, silly.

43:25.746 --> 43:30.917
He sent her husband away
into battle where he was killed.
Second samuel, verse 15.

43:30.952 --> 43:32.919
Monsieur, your car
is waiting.

43:32.954 --> 43:36.756
Tell him I'll be
right- right there.

43:39.593 --> 43:42.762
I don't want anything
to happen to you.

43:44.765 --> 43:48.701
The only thing that ever
happens to me is that I just-

43:48.769 --> 43:50.937
I miss you too much.

43:57.778 --> 44:00.480
Do you really have to be gone
for two whole weeks?

44:00.547 --> 44:02.482
Yes, I do, baby.

44:02.549 --> 44:05.986
Well, that's enough time
for you to convince them
to abandon nuclear weapons.

44:06.053 --> 44:07.988
Yes, it is.
You bet.

44:08.055 --> 44:09.990
Ooh, daddy.
What?

44:10.057 --> 44:13.493
Will you call me every night
just before I go to bed?

44:13.560 --> 44:15.495
No, it's too expensive.

44:15.562 --> 44:17.563
of course, I will.

44:18.565 --> 44:20.500
I love you.
I love you too.

44:20.567 --> 44:22.568
<i>Bye, daddy, bye.
Be good.</i>

44:48.595 --> 44:50.863
Hundred sixty
millimeter mortars...

44:50.931 --> 44:52.865
About the strength
of two hand grenades.

44:52.933 --> 44:55.035
Don't worry though.
They're all spent.

44:55.102 --> 44:59.272
They used
to train g.I.S back here
in the second world war.

45:05.046 --> 45:07.147
You can't tell anybody
about this place.

45:07.214 --> 45:09.382
Never.

45:10.717 --> 45:12.985
I like it.

45:13.054 --> 45:15.488
I wouldn't want
to live here, but...

45:15.556 --> 45:17.490
It's nice.

45:17.558 --> 45:20.060
It's private.

45:21.895 --> 45:24.497
Let's get hitched
and live here forever.

45:24.565 --> 45:29.202
To an army man?
They're too weird.

45:29.570 --> 45:35.007
Last year, colonel harris
took his family to nevada
to watch the a-bomb go off.

45:35.076 --> 45:37.009
That was their vacation.

45:37.078 --> 45:39.512
<i>Look, I'm not ashamed
of what they're doing.</i>

45:39.580 --> 45:42.515
I mean,
the manhattan project
ended the last war.

45:42.583 --> 45:45.185
Maybe project blue sky
will prevent the next one.

45:45.252 --> 45:47.220
Do you know why
they call it blue sky?

45:47.588 --> 45:50.690
They're gonna detonate
a big one underground
to track radiation.

45:50.757 --> 45:53.693
But you can't see radiation,

45:53.760 --> 45:57.197
You can't feel it
or taste it or smell it.

45:57.264 --> 46:00.133
So only a handful of people will
actually know where it is...

46:00.201 --> 46:03.603
And the rest of the country
could be swimming in the stuff,

46:03.604 --> 46:06.739
But for all they know
the sky is just
as blue as ever.

46:07.108 --> 46:09.609
Yeah, well, what
they don't know
won't hurt them.

46:12.045 --> 46:15.482
No wonder west point
snapped you up.

46:15.549 --> 46:19.152
And if I married you,
I'd end up just like my mom.

46:19.220 --> 46:21.887
Yeah, you talk gibberish
sometimes, alex.

46:27.394 --> 46:30.079
- Catch.
- No!

46:34.635 --> 46:36.302
What the hell was that?

46:36.370 --> 46:38.505
They weren't supposed
to start maneuvers
for another two weeks.

46:38.572 --> 46:41.274
Well, maybe them cubans
sprung a sneak attack.

46:50.166 --> 46:53.001
Jesus.
Let's get the hell
out of here.

47:30.973 --> 47:33.809
<i>What in the hell are you
doing here, mister?</i>

47:48.325 --> 47:50.492
What do you know?
What's happening?

47:56.499 --> 48:00.202
Calm down, calm down.
Everything's under control.
It's all right.

48:00.269 --> 48:03.205
Alex, honey, are you okay?

48:03.272 --> 48:06.709
Vince, I think we gotta take
him to the hospital it looks
like he needs stitches.

48:06.776 --> 48:08.877
<i>Let's see.
And he needs a swift kick
in the butt even more.</i>

48:08.945 --> 48:10.879
Are you hurt?
No.

48:10.947 --> 48:12.881
<i>Excuse me, I'd like
to apologize for my son.</i>

48:12.949 --> 48:16.218
I'm afraid he was off-limits
with your daughter.

48:16.285 --> 48:18.554
Well, boys will be boys.

48:18.621 --> 48:23.225
Yeah. I'd like
this area secured now.
Nobody goes in or out.

48:23.292 --> 48:25.361
<i>Go home, everybody.
The show's over.</i>

48:27.296 --> 48:30.065
<i>I want to know what you
were doing up there.</i>

48:30.132 --> 48:34.069
Just what you told me to do.
Making friends with glenn.

48:34.136 --> 48:37.740
I want to know exactly
what the two of you
were doing up there.

48:37.807 --> 48:39.975
What do you mean by "exactly"?

48:40.343 --> 48:44.646
Well, was an old grenade
the only thing that went off?

48:44.881 --> 48:47.249
